May 21 2006	great location	We recently spent four nights in London at the Knightsbridge Green Hotel and would return again in a minute. The 2 room suite we had was just perfect for that length of visit. The rooms were nicely sized and allowed a great deal of privacy if one wanted to read or watch TV and the other wanted to nap -- a very nice option after 2 weeks on the road. But the thing we loved the most was the hotel's proximity to so many other sites! If you go there, you'll want to know that the #9 bus that you can catch right across the street, will take you to Piccadilly Circus, Trafalgar Square, even all the way to the theater district! It runs all the time and is a wonderful way to see London and get to all the locations that would be a bit too far to walk. We used it several times and were very impressed with its speed and comfort. Also, to get to Victoria Station or even Waterloo Station to catch trains, etc. is just a 15 minute or so cab ride. All in all a great location and hotel!	
