Jan 24 2006	Excellent location satisfactory hotel	We stayed here for 2 nights in January.The best thing about this hotel is the location - major bus routes go along Knightsbridge outside, and there is a tube station 2 minutes walk away (when open - see later!). Harvey Nichols and Harrods are just around the corner, Hyde Park is over the road, and some of London's best-known museums are within walking distance.The hotel itself is unpretentious and the staff are friendly. The room prices are cheaper than most in central London, though dear compared to other cities.We had a large room, on the 4th floor so traffic noise was minimal. The plumbing was slightly antiquated but this added to the charm!The only downsides were:- when we arrived we had previously discovered that a large part of the Piccadilly Line would be closed for the weekend, including Knightsbridge Tube Station. The reception staff seemed to know little or nothing about this, and we had to go and find an explanatory leaflet on the Tube itself- full English breakfast was £12 each. It was delivered to your room and very nice, but just around the corner at Benji's (opposite Harrods) you can get a very tasty cooked breakfast for £1.99!But overall it was a perfectly acceptable hotel, and better than many.	
