Jul 25 2005	Knightsbridge Green - Outstanding value location and service	Stayed for 3 nights at this hotel in July 2005. Staff was very, very friendly. Check-in was a 1-minute process. I have stayed in many hotels and I was simply not expecting what I found - a large, brightly lit suite, a very, very large bedroom with high ceilings and a very large comfortable king-size bed, and finally, a fabulous, large, ultra-clean bathroom with heated towel racks. The living room had large double-pane windows overlooking the street, a breakfast table, TV, and a convertible sofa. Both the living room and bedroom had nice, pleasant cream colored tones and tasteful decoration. Since we were with an 18-month old baby, the staff had already set up a crib in the bedroom with nice sheets and a pillow. All of the staff members we ecountered were very nice, always smiling and provided great service. When I asked if we could store some milk in the hotel, they immediately offered to set up a small refridgerator in our suite, and got it done in 5 minutes. The location of the hotel is as good as it gets. The tube is hardly a minutes walk. Hyde park is literally across the street and a children's playground is almost opposite the hotel (a 2-minute walk). Harrods is around the corner (4-minute walk). All of the best shops and many, many great restaurants are just several doors away. The hotel does not have other facilities like gyms, etc. but if you are visiting as a tourist, you simply cannot go wrong by staying at this lovely hotel. The hotel has a small (5-person) elevator that is very quick and almost always available in seconds. This hotel definitely made our stay in London a memorable experience, and I would happily go back in the future. I have added a photo of Knightsbridge where the hotel is located. On the photo, the hotel is directly behind the red double-decker bus. To the left of the bus is where a tube stop is.	
