Mar 6 2005	Great Rates; Very Friendly Staff	Stayed there in late February, 2005. Hotel has a great location on Knightsbridge, near the tube stop, Harrods and the Museums (short bus ride or walk). The staff were extremely friendly, pleasant and helpful. The rooms (2 standard doubles) were quite nice, and very spacious (particularly for London!). The room rates of 115 pounds was also very good. Breakfast is not included, and is typically expensive, but is very nice, and is delivered to your room, as there is no common dining room. You specify the time you would like it delivered, and it arrived exactly when we had asked for it. One of the rooms overlooked the central fire escapes, which weren't too scenic, but that didn't matter to us as we weren't in the room much. The 'interior' room overlooking the fire escapes was quiet at all times, even with the window open. The 'outer' room, overlooking Knightsbridge was quiet unless you opened the window, in which case some traffic noise came in. All rooms have air conditioning. Will definitely return next time I'm in London.	
